Oh no!  White can now play QxPh7#.  (That hash mark "#" means "game over").
Nf6 won't do it, white could push a pawn.  You must move g6 or h6, or you risk losing.
You could have gotten away with f5 too (momentarily), but white is unlikely to pass up checkmate much longer.
